{
  "local_port": 50842,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some recipes using 4 ounces of steak?",
  "response": "Here are a few delicious recipes that you can make using 4 ounces of steak:\n\n### 1. **Steak Salad**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (flank or sirloin works best)\n- Mixed greens (like arugula or spinach)\n- Cherry tomatoes, halved\n- Cucumber, sliced\n- Red onion, thinly sliced\n- Your favorite salad dressing (balsamic vinaigrette recommended)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Season the steak with salt and pepper. Cook it to your desired level of doneness on a grill or in a skillet (about 3-4 minutes per side for medium rare).\n2. Let the steak rest for a few minutes, then slice it thinly against the grain.\n3. In a large bowl, combine the mixed greens, tomatoes, cucumber, and red onion.\n4. Add the sliced steak on top and drizzle with your favorite dressing before serving.\n\n### 2. **Steak Tacos**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (flank or skirt steak recommended)\n- 2 small corn or flour tortillas\n- 1/4 avocado, sliced\n- Salsa or pico de gallo\n- Fresh cilantro, chopped\n- Lime wedges\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Season the steak with salt, pepper, and any other spices you prefer (like cumin or chili powder).\n2. Cook the steak in a skillet over medium-high heat for 3-4 minutes on each side, depending on thickness.\n3. Let it rest, then slice it thinly.\n4. Heat the tortillas in a separate pan or microwave.\n5. Assemble the tacos by placing steak slices, avocado, salsa, and cilantro on the tortillas. Squeeze lime juice over the top before serving.\n\n### 3. **Steak Stir-Fry**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (sirloin or ribeye)\n- 2 cups mixed vegetables (like bell peppers, broccoli, and snap peas)\n- 1 tablespoon soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon oyster sauce (optional)\n- 1 teaspoon ginger, minced\n- 1 teaspoon garlic, minced\n- Cooked rice or noodles\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Slice the steak thinly against the grain.\n2. Heat a little oil in a frying pan or wok over high heat. Add the ginger and garlic, cooking for about 30 seconds.\n3. Add the steak and stir-fry for 2-3 minutes until browned.\n4. Add the mixed vegetables and cook for an additional 3-4 minutes.\n5. Stir in the soy sauce and oyster sauce, cooking until everything is well-coated and heated through.\n6. Serve over rice or noodles.\n\n### 4. **Steak and Eggs**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (sirloin or ribeye)\n- 2 eggs\n- Salt and pepper\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil or butter\n- Fresh herbs (like chives or parsley) for garnish\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Season the steak with salt and pepper. In a skillet, heat the olive oil or butter over medium-high heat.\n2. Cook the steak for 3-4 minutes on each side for medium-rare. Remove from the skillet and let it rest.\n3. In the same skillet, crack the eggs and cook them to your liking (sunny side up, over easy, etc.).\n4. Slice the steak and serve it alongside the eggs. Garnish with fresh herbs.\n\n### Enjoy!\nThese recipes are creative and easy to prepare, allowing you to enjoy a variety of flavors while making the most out of your 4 ounces of steak!",
